Comment: I lost most of my inheritance through a dishonest brother (R), a crooked lawyer (his) and an incompetent Estate Administrator (another lawyer).

There were two types of assets. A large, valuable house and garden and bank accounts.

The intended executor died shortly after my Mother. Another brother (G) had a mortgage on the house and we four brothers were listed as co-owners. G looked after the sale of the house and dispersed the funds equitably. Being sick he couldn't be the executor. Brother R assumed the position but eventually handed the matter over to a 'professional'. R also produced a 'forced'/coerced Will.

This 'professional' took just under 10 years to administer the Estate,  charging $400,000 for the 'work'. She paid out money to two brothers and G and I were left with crumbs.

Bottom line:
1. Always appoint TWO trusted executors  and make sure they are YOUNGER than the Estate owner;
2. Copy the (final) Will to all parties;
3. Expect fireworks;
4. Never trust siblings!

